{
  "stem": "20083.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 15.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The following morning I was out and I saw the smashed windows, because that happened mostly during the night.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's why they call it Kristall Night, Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The smashing of the windows really took place after sundown.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I stayed at home, yes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I had no, except for my father, who already had had the stroke and who was home at the Kurfurstendamm.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had no relatives in Berlin except my immediate family-- my sister and my mother.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And nothing had happened to them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But of course, the damage was enormous as far as the stores were concerned, because it was actually all the window panes were broken.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, my father had two brothers, Otto, who emigrated with his family to China, to Canton in China, where he died later of cancer.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Ernst, who, in 1937 or 1936, I cannot remember the exact year, committed suicide because his practice was taken from him.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was a medical doctor, too.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And on my father's side, almost the same thing happened.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My mother had two brothers, Hans Fraenkel, who moved from Italy to Switzerland, and the other uncle, or rather my mother's brother, Max, who was a medical doctor and also committed suicide because he could no longer support his family, which consisted of a wife, Lotte, and two daughters, Ilse and Ursula Fraenkel.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, the reason why he first moved to Italy is because he became the commercial correspondent for the a newspaper, a daily newspaper in Germany, which still exists, incidentally, a very highly respected newspaper.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He became the commercial correspondent, first in Milano, in Italy.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then later he moved because of the anti-- the fascist anti-semitic laws in 1938.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When Mussolini became a great close ally of Hitler, he moved to Switzerland to save his own life.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
